The calculation involves three components: e0 combines the current price with the previous e0 value, e1 incorporates the difference between price and current e0 with the previous e1, and e2 layers in the phase ratio and prior jma value along with the squared alpha terms. Finally, jma adds the current e2 to the previous jma value.

